Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is posted here\Nthis early in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:13.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysterious figure making a\N stir at Kanyasai Phantom Thief Jumoji
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they must be in high gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.95,0:00:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they can't top me when it\Ncomes to being geared up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.03,0:00:19.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Global Act Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Fukube! You're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.00,0:00:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be hard to keep\NJumoji at large like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.60,0:00:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're really making an effort,\Nstaking out so early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.93,0:00:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there are this many aspiring\Ndetectives waiting around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.85,0:00:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it looks like the crime\Nhasn't happened yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Jumoji,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.19,0:00:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you're going to come, then come!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.12,0:01:13.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:19.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.14,0:01:25.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.73,0:01:31.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.65,0:01:38.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.28,0:01:46.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:54.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:02:01.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:08.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.69,0:02:16.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:26.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Final Target
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the final\Nday at last. The moment of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like I've met that\Nlady somewhere before...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:03:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The idea of using the\NJumoji incident as bait
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.32,0:03:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to sell our volumes of\N{\i1}Hyouka {\i0}isn't a bad one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, it won't be enough\Nfor us to sell out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.87,0:03:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure it will work, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.55,0:03:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Jumoji's target the\NQuiz Club? No, it couldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could he steal from the Quiz Club\Nonce the event is already over?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.48,0:03:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of this. I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've had enough, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.78,0:03:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened, Phantom Thief Jumoji?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if anything happens, text me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scared off by too many people here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! Lousy Jumoji! He put on a feint!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A feint? You mean, the Quiz Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:03:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the {\i1}Keion {\i0}[Light Music] Club.\NOne of their {\i1}gen {\i0}[strings] is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Light Music Club? The Light Music Club?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure about this, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.89,0:04:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you think,\Ngo ahead and check for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.94,0:04:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the\NLight Music Club got hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jumoji's flexibility is far greater\Nthan I anticipated, or can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The frontal approach didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to rethink this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else can I do besides\Ncatch him in the act?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:38.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Goal: Sell out all 200 copies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.29,0:04:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When they sell, they sell well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 20 that we relegated away sold out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Chitanda took ten more\Nof them down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Add to that nine more this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have some hope for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Saturday for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.06,0:05:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see you've devoted yourself to the\Nenergy-conserving work, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis? You really did come, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.11,0:05:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be grateful that\Nyour big sister came to see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how her dear younger\Nbrother was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.21,0:05:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What's that?\NIt doesn't suit you very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.88,0:05:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Warashibe Protocol.\NYour fountain pen became a hand mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? So in other words,\Nyou exchanged stuff for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.72,0:05:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.14,0:05:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take this. In return...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Corpse By Evening{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.36,0:05:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a manga?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's up to you whether or not\Nyou pass the time with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.83,0:05:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Anshinin Takuha"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What did you think of {\i1}A Corpse By Evening{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.64,0:06:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it turned out\Nquite well, if I do say so myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.14,0:06:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I just helped out\Nwith the backgrounds
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.81,0:06:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and didn't have much\Nto do with it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you enjoyed reading this manga,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the credit goes to the author\Nand the artist, not me."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess "Anshinin Takuha" must\Nbe like the name of their team.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's not as though all of us\Nare in the Manga Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just liked manga, seemed to\Nhit it off while talking to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when we decided that we\Nwould try drawing something up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.34,0:06:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this is the story that came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's quite extraordinary\Nfor a maiden effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it wouldn't be right for me\Nto blow their horn for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will leave it in your hands\Nto judge its worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:07:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we have no intention of\Nsplitting up after just one work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have already started something\Nnew with next year's Kanyasai in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.65,0:07:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our writer, A, is thinking of turning\Nthe writing style on its ear
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is talking about tackling\Nsome kind of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear the plan is a take on one\Nof Christie's ultra-famous works
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.78,0:07:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while seeing if a twist or two\Ncan't be added to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.79,0:07:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title has already been chosen,\Nso I'll announce it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next story's title will be\N{\i1}The Kudryavka Sequence{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet another foreboding name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.92,0:07:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, see you next year\Nduring Kanyasai season again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anshinin Takuha."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"{\i1}The Kudryavka Sequence{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what "Kudryavka" means,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that word "Sequence"\Nthere catches my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also Christie's ultra-famous work?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:52.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,See you next year
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.99,0:07:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's up to you whether\Nor not you pass the time with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:08:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Sis. I hope you haven't\Nlaid more trouble at my doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.50,0:08:03.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Broadcasting Studio
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Um, you are the\NBroadcasting Club's president,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.34,0:08:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshino-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.93,0:08:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Chitanda Eru, president of\Nthe Classic Lit Club. Yoshino-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.31,0:08:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the president of\Nthe Classic Lit Club?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.40,0:08:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing! I was just\Nabout to come see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.94,0:08:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to be our guest\Non the radio at lunchtime?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think having the president\Nof Jumoji's final target on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be a huge hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.41,0:08:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't ask for a better chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be my pleasure to be on your show!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, 12:00 here at the studio, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The broadcast starts\Nat 12:30! See you then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.88,0:08:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.93,0:09:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for being here. Have there\Nbeen any new developments?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ku" has been skipped over;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a {\i1}gen {\i0}[string] from the {\i1}Keion\N{\i0}[Light Music] Club was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to rethink this from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.95,0:09:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's all wrapped up in that {\i1}doujin {\i0}manga\Nand has been like this for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.55,0:09:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.84,0:09:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That picture... it feels like\NI've seen it somewhere before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.35,0:09:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes are fooling you.\NMy sister brought this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, this isn't the time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.61,0:09:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the tip of my tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.19,0:09:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swallow it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.45,0:09:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.11,0:09:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you do {\i1}something{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.41,0:10:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see another page.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.75,0:10:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This picture looks just like the poster\Noutside the conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, it sure does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.10,0:10:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, let me borrow\Nthis manga for a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go compare the two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. But bring it right\Nback here. I kind of need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.49,0:10:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:38.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the Manga Club
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the artwork, here, all right.\NYes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.49,0:10:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.\NSorry, it's not for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, could I take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just draw whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.75,0:10:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.42,0:10:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, the color should be...\NI'm going to go change your water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, mm-hm. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.01,0:11:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said no pictures!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops!\NNice!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry, Ibara!\NThis isn't what I intended...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.46,0:11:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm. It's okay. It's khaki to\Nbegin with. This won't stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.27,0:11:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.57,0:12:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, President. I hope\Nyou can do without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to change out of your\NRainbow Parakeet outfit, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a moment\Nright now? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gym clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I changed clothes.\NSo, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.19,0:12:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why do you have this, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.03,0:12:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't mine... it belongs to Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.66,0:12:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does Oreki have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said his sister brought it.\NMayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you know this manga?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.75,0:12:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, well, yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a poster promoting\Nthe culture festival
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.13,0:12:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm curious as to whether\Nwhoever drew that poster
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.92,0:13:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and whoever drew this\Nmanga are the same person!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this poster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next to the conference room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:14.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shuubun{\i0} ('Middle of Autumn')\NWhen light\Nfindeth equal measure with darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:14.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:15.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,54th Kanyasai
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ninety-nine percent it's the same person. The\Nway the ears are handled is exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to get that off my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were curious, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.50,0:13:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, you want to ask who drew it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm curious about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.51,0:13:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Tanabe-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.93,0:13:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You're, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes. So, did you\Nneed something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:13:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us for asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but do you know who drew the poster\Nthat's pinned up right there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.65,0:14:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that would be Kugayama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Kugayama Muneyoshi-{\i1}san{\i0}?\NThe student council president?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.11,0:14:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I badgered him\Nto draw something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turned out nicely, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I think it looks very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.25,0:14:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be tickled to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.46,0:14:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First I find out the author,\Nnow I learn who the artist is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.17,0:14:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll ask him about it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.17,0:14:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? Maybe this golden\Ncombo will keep on rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.14,0:14:31.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, was it the same person? Wait, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, gym clothes?\NWhat about the Manga Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I switched out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the same person!\NWe even found out his name!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho, good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Kugayama Muneyoshi-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NWhat a surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he famous?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hotaro, you're messing with us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.79,0:15:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.63,0:15:08.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kugayama Muneyoshi (Student\NCouncil President)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The student council president.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.35,0:15:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was pronounced\N"Rikuyama" this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.97,0:15:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that among\Nthis Anshinin Takuha group,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.69,0:15:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this Kugayama guy drew the pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "Anshinin"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You read that as "Ajimu."\NIt's a location in Kyushu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that vital knowledge\Nfor getting through life?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.70,0:15:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reading for this is written in\Nsmall Roman letters next to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artwork was done\Nby Kugayama-{\i1}senpai{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the story was written by\Nsomeone named Anjo Haruna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.13,0:15:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you know about this, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.50,0:15:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love that manga. I bought it\Nat last year's culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Ibara to come out and say\Nshe loves something, it must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Oreki,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.43,0:15:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could I borrow that for a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine with me, but in a\Nlittle while. I still need to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it happens, I'm appearing on the\NBroadcasting Club's lunchtime show!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.45,0:16:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, that's amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice going. You even managed\Nto score an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The goal of selling out of\N{\i1}Hyouka {\i0}is now within sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.24,0:16:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll teach you the secrets\Nto being a good guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.71,0:16:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First and foremost, a guest\Nonly gets about five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the question is, how much can\Nyou stand out in that short time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.68,0:16:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting Around at Kanyasai,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.39,0:16:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the second thing is, keep\Nsaying "The Classic Lit Club."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.09,0:16:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Gardening Club, the Cooking Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.97,0:16:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! You can count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Light Music Club,\NChristie's ultra-famous work,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll be doing that, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Kudryavka Sequence"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.32,0:16:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.78,0:16:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. My thinking was\Ncoming to a standstill anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, I'd move my thinking\Nforward by talking to these guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.13,0:17:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Chitanda would hamper that.\NIf she knew what I was trying to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm positive that she'd be against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but could you come\Nwith me for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've figured something out,\Nhaven't you, Hotaro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.19,0:17:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one asked you to\Nexercise your instincts!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.98,0:17:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Chitanda's got that\Nlook in her eye, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.61,0:17:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you realized something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.61,0:17:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I haven't, I haven't!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, this isn't about the Jumoji matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.59,0:17:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very curious about this, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.34,0:17:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so why will you only\Ntalk to Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, man... Well, I guess at this point...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does indeed have to do\Nwith the Jumoji matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, include us, as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.90,0:18:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's of an incredibly obscene\Nnature. Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tell me what this\N"obscene" story of yours is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to have to drag\Nyou out here like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it doesn't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I had any\Nearth-shattering thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.38,0:18:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that there are a number\Nof things I can't get my head around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to me like they\Nought to be significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some hidden link between\Nthe clubs that fell victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not that, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, did you find some tiny mistake\Nthe phantom thief Jumoji made?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not quite that, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.44,0:18:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's neither one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.95,0:18:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are over 1,000 suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.95,0:19:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really supposed\Nto identify the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without finding any leads or mistakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.41,0:19:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's not as though I\Nhave anything on the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to gather\Nmy thoughts a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.47,0:19:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm? Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.76,0:19:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to this, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First off,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.44,0:19:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why is Jumoji stealing ten different\Nthings from ten different clubs?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just something we assumed from\Nreading the way he signed his notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An assumption that now\Nseems to be in doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, why is he leaving greeting\Ncards at the scene of his crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean these.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.20,0:19:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Third, why is he using the word "lost"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,lost
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.42,0:19:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't one normally say "taken," instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.05,0:19:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourth, why leave behind a\N"Getting Around at Kanyasai" book?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.05,0:20:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the only thing that\Nhas a list of all the clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.84,0:20:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why choose that in particular?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I have that, too...\NThe one from the Cooking Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.81,0:20:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifth, why the Gardening Club\Nand the Cooking Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a number of other clubs\Nthat begin with "E" and "O."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially with the {\i1}Oryori {\i0}[Cooking] Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, you'd just consider\Nthat the {\i1}Ryori {\i0}Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That directly touches on the question
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of whether the Classic Lit Club or\Nthe Industrial Arts Club will be hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixth... and this is the weirdest one...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he skip "Ku"\Nand steal from "Ke" next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.66,0:20:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was to get by without being noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Global Act Club was in\Nno condition to steal from.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh, there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.50,0:20:39.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Christie's ultra-famous work
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.88,0:20:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The manga has nothing\Nto do with this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may not necessarily be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, what do you think of when you\Nhear "Christie's ultra-famous work"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.01,0:20:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... {\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Murder On the Orient Express{\i0},\N{\i1}The Murder of Roger Ackroyd{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:20:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and {\i1}The A.B.C. Murders{\i0}.\NThose four, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.73,0:21:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone were going to work\None of them into a manga,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.19,0:21:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and give it the title\N{\i1}The Kudryavka Sequence,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.66,0:21:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be {\i1}The A.B.C. Murders{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudryavka was the dog they put in\Na rocket as an experiment long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.08,0:21:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but then she never made it back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, given the\Nimage of a violent death,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd guess {\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since this is just supposition,\Nwe don't have to pin it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm starting to figure out\Nwhat you're trying to say, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, is there a manga called\N{\i1}The Kudryavka Sequence{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being sold at the culture festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. The Executive Committee\Nwasn't told of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was coming out\Nthrough the Manga Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka would have mentioned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.69,0:21:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If," you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At last year's culture festival,\N{\i1}A Corpse By Evening {\i0}came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.82,0:21:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the afterword, it announced that\Nthere would be a manga next year
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.70,0:21:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was a twist on Christie's\Nultra-famous work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.04,0:21:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We guessed that that work was\N{\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.58,0:22:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or {\i1}The A.B.C. Murders{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.59,0:22:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, this year, when it was\Nannounced for, there are incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which clearly seem to be lifted from\N{\i1}The A.B.C. Murders {\i0}taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.18,0:22:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.10,0:22:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Hotaro, you're\Nsaying that these Jumoji incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were announced at the end of\N{\i1}A Corpse By Evening{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.90,0:22:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, enough that I'm not willing\Nto say they're completely unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.77,0:22:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.23,0:22:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even get the feeling that\Nwith Jumoji, it's more like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.49,0:22:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he wants to carry out this Jumoji\Ncaper while causing as little trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.20,0:22:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and while being hindered\Nas little as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.16,0:22:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's being\Ndone for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.16,0:22:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, why did he skip over "Ku"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.45,0:22:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were any number\Nof ways to pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.21,0:22:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, there's some reason\Nbehind these incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.13,0:22:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm concerned about Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay. Go on. I'm going to\Nlook over this stuff you gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:22:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.23,0:23:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Chitanda to have some\N"Ko" items ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.82,0:23:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bait to lure the culprit in with,\Nright? I was thinking of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.24,0:23:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get some {\i1}koryogenko\N{\i0}[proofed manuscripts] ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.00,0:23:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have high hopes, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.13,0:23:30.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,On Air
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start when we get our cue, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.39,0:23:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.52,0:23:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4... 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.15,0:23:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a special edition of\NYoshino Yasukuni's Radio Beat!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.15,0:23:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, hello there! This is radio\Npersonality Yoshino Yasukuni.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.28,0:23:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our guest for the final day is\Nthe Classic Lit Club's president
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.24,0:23:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from Class 1-A, Chitanda Eru-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right! I-It's a\Npleasure to talk to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.79,0:24:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.27,0:24:26.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.94,0:24:29.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.61,0:24:35.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.57,0:24:37.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.83,0:24:43.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:48.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.42,0:24:55.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.22,0:24:59.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.89,0:25:05.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.48,0:25:10.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.19,0:25:17.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.74,0:25:23.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.41,0:25:30.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.59,0:25:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Kudryavka Sequence."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.93,0:25:43.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kudryavka Sequence
